author: @hmgclipz6808

Comment:
¬†@hmgclipz6808¬† I see you're choosing to separate the tragedy (as the cause) and the scars (as the effect). That's one interpretation, and I respect that. But in this case you can just as easily interpret them as being the same/or atleast interchangeable. I'll use your own example: Batman's parents were killed and that caused him immense grief that led to him becoming a superhero.

You can either say "The grief of his parents dying led to him becoming a superhero. (the scar of grief made him who he is / defined a huge part of who he is)

Or you can say, "The death of his parents led to him becoming a superhero." (The tragedy defined a huge part of who he is)

Both statements are factually correct, and essentially convey the same meaning with only slight differences, and have the same end result. The tragedy led to scars and the scars defined him. So in turn the tragedy did define him, because without the tragedy the scars wouldn't exist.

Objectively scars and tragedy should be different. But HERE, they're so similar that the dialogue just seems contradictory and even a bit silly. üòÇ
Just the fact that we're having such a lengthy discussion about it is more proof that it is ambiguous and can be interpreted in more than one way. Peace ‚úåüèª

Comment: The resounding drums, triumphant brass, and sweeping strings of epic music inject movie trailers with a profoundly thrilling ambience. This style of bold, operatic composition brings an unmatched sense of grandeur. The full symphonic sound washes over you, instant goosebumps as that exhilarating melody unfurls. No words are needed to feel the mood - whether tensions simmering into war cries or heroes rising against the odds to turn the tide. The music amplifies the high stakes hinted onscreen into palpable excitement. These epic anthems punctuate trailers with exclamation points, ensuring the adventure ahead leaves an indelible impression whether it features clashing armies or character-driven drama. The marriage of epic music's unrelenting crescendo and carefully edited visuals forms a siren song, drawing us right into imagined new worlds brimming with action, emotion and spectacle. Who can resist such powerful musical storytelling, the ultimate appetizer promising grand purpose behind these tales? We have those ingenious sound composers to thank for trailers that spark such strong senses of destiny through their triumphant symphonic suites alone - our hearts quicken and imaginations ignite.
